The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Colts turn to down SA

A STAFF REPORTER

 Debabrata Das scored 66 .. 

Calcutta: India continued their emphatic run by winning their second match on the trot after they crushed South Africa by 102 runs in the under-19 Afro-Asian meet at the Port Stadium in Visakhapatnam on Sunday. India beat Bangladesh by four wickets in the tournament opener on Saturday. 

According to the information received here, an unbeaten knock of 66 round by Calcutta boy Debabrata Das helped India to pile up 253 for six. Piyush Chawla made 54 and captain Ravi Kant Shukla contributed 39. 

For the Proteas, Ryan Jaftha and Richard Das Neves picked up three and two wickets respectively. 

While chasing the South African batting crumbled for a paltry 151 in 36.4 overs due to some excellent spin bowling by Piyush Chawla and Shahbaz Nadeem. 

BRIEF SCORES 

India 253/6 (Debabrata Das 66 . ., Piyush Chawla 54, Ravi Kant Shukla 39; Ryan Jaftha 3/53) South Africa 151 all out (Schyff Van Der 53, Peter Daniel 26, Elgar Dean 32; Piyush Chawla 3/28, Shahbaz Nadeem 2/31, Sourav Bandekar 2/31). India won by 102 runs. 




